{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nField evidence since the 2026-07-08 plan-review recalibration (782 runs / 225 tickets): 18% of tickets need 4+ review rounds and the sticky tail consumes 60% of gate compute; 38 PASS->BLOCK flips (22 remediation-induced, 16 pure sampling-miss); 32% verdict instability on byte-identical plans; 95% of remediation edits mint new findings (net +324 across 430 edit rounds). The shipped cross-round convergence machinery — the plan-review rising floor (epic 7d43, children ec89/cc5b) and the code-review region-gated floor (ADR 0037) — is INERT behind default-False flags. The operator has authorized flipping both flags ON BY DEFAULT on this field evidence (superseding the discriminates_novelty-eval prerequisite), with a follow-up task (49ae-258b-4534-4d83) to remove the flags entirely.\n\n## What\n- In src/rebar/_config_schema.py flip `remediation_mode: bool = False` -> `True` (line 264) and `novelty_drop_active: bool = False` -> `True` (line 282).\n- Rewrite the adjacent comments to default-ON framing with explicit-false as the back-out. Verbatim stale text to replace: lines 262-263 'Default OFF for v1 (expand-contract: ship off → validate on the dogfood corpus → flip in a follow-up); off/absent restores byte-identical full-review behavior.' and lines 278-281 'The EVIDENCE GATE: the rising floor stays inert (gate runs un-floored) until this is flipped true — done MANUALLY by the operator only after 150b's `discriminates_novelty` eval has cleared its bar (`rebar prompt eval plan-review-novelty`). Default False (a third gate on top of remediation_mode + per-review eligibility), so the floor never drops a finding by default.'\n- SHARED GATE — intentional cross-gate effect: `novelty_drop_active` is consumed by BOTH plan-review (src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:204) AND the code-review region-gated floor (src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py:608 via src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py:720). Flipping it by default activates the code-review floor too; this is deliberate and included in the operator authorization.\n- Update ALL stale default-OFF docstrings/comments in source (complete sweep, verified by grep):\n  - src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:81 ('off/absent (default-OFF v1 rollout)' -> default-ON; explicit false is the back-out)\n  - src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:188-195 (the `_maybe_apply_rising_floor` docstring: 'flipped only after 150b's discriminates_novelty eval clears its bar). By default the flag is False, so the floor is inert and the verdict byte-identical' -> default-ON (operator-authorized 2026-07-11); explicit false restores the byte-identical full review)\n  - src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:~523 (the '(config remediation_mode + per-review eligibility + verify.novelty_drop_active); inert (and the verdict byte-identical) by default.' comment -> active by default; triple gate still applies per-review)\n  - src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py:597 and :608 ('the shared evidence gate, OFF by default' docstring + '(off by default)' inline comment -> ON by default; explicit false is the back-out)\n- Update docs to the True defaults, recording the operator-authorized flip in lieu of the discriminates_novelty eval:\n  - docs/config.md (~lines 107-118: verify.remediation_mode / verify.novelty_drop_active entries)\n  - docs/plan-review-gate.md (~lines 322-338 prose incl. line 329 '(default off)', and the ~370-374 default table)\n  - docs/review-kernel.md (~line 124: 'It is OFF by default (gated on the shared verify.novelty_drop_active)' -> ON by default)\n  - docs/adr/0008-convergent-plan-edit-re-review.md (~lines 55, 88-96) and docs/adr/0037-code-review-novelty-convergence.md (~lines 92, 167): add a dated 'defaults flipped ON (operator-authorized on field evidence, 2026-07-11)' note rather than rewriting ADR history.\n- Update stale default assertions in tests: tests/unit/test_plan_review_rising_floor.py:166 (`assert vc.novelty_drop_active is False`) and tests/unit/test_plan_review_remediation_gate.py:192 (`assert vc.remediation_mode is False`) — both flip to `is True`.\n- NON-GOALS: completion_floor_active (epic 66ac, separate evidence gate) stays False; novelty_drop_threshold (0.7) / novelty_priority_floor (0.4) / remediation_window_minutes (60) unchanged; no change to the floor math or eligibility logic.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] VerifyConfig.remediation_mode defaults to True in src/rebar/_config_schema.py:264.\n- [ ] VerifyConfig.novelty_drop_active defaults to True in src/rebar/_config_schema.py:282.\n- [ ] Setting either key to false in config restores byte-identical full-review behavior (the off-path/triple-gate tests, which pass explicit False configs, run unmodified in behavior).\n- [ ] tests/unit/test_plan_review_rising_floor.py:166 asserts `vc.novelty_drop_active is True`.\n- [ ] tests/unit/test_plan_review_remediation_gate.py:192 asserts `vc.remediation_mode is True`.\n- [ ] Every source location in the 'complete sweep' list above (\\_config_schema.py, plan_review/__init__.py:81/188-195/~523, code_review/workflow_ops.py:597/608) carries default-ON framing with explicit-false named as the back-out.\n- [ ] docs/config.md, docs/plan-review-gate.md, and docs/review-kernel.md reflect the True defaults.\n- [ ] docs/plan-review-gate.md records that the flip was operator-authorized on field evidence in lieu of the discriminates_novelty eval.\n- [ ] docs/adr/0008 and docs/adr/0037 carry a dated defaults-flipped note.\n- [ ] completion_floor_active remains default False.\n- [ ] make lint passes on the change.\n- [ ] make typecheck passes on the change.\n- [ ] make test passes on the change."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783832326398966001,"uuid":"c7e06a66-9c69-4221-94aa-6033fd1c24a0"}